1. install required libraries:

libx11-dev libxtst-dev libxt-dev libsm-dev libxpm-dev ncurses-dev

1.5. locate where the required packages install their files with:

dpkg-query -L libxtst-dev

2. configure and specify where X includes and libraries are located:

./configure --with-x --x-includes=/usr/include/X11/ --x-libraries=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/

3. check if configuration includes X 
after

grep X11 src/auto/config.h

the response should look like

#define HAVE_X11

and not like

/* #undef HAVE_X11 */

4. after compiling vim, check its options to ensure that
vim --version

+clipboard
